  "text": "Intracellular RNA from WNV-infected cells was shown to contain two types of pathogenassociated molecular patterns (PAMPs), 5′ triphosphate (cleaved RNA fragments and uncapped full length genome RNA) and dsRNAs, that were able to activate the cytoplasmic sensors RIG-I and MDA5 [CITATION_1] . In this study, no activation was detected after transfection of 3′ or 5′ genome RNA fragments. A different study found that several different short, in vitro transcribed WNV genome fragments were able to induce low level activation of the RIG-I after transfection into cells, with the 5′ genome fragment showing the highest level of activation [CITATION_2] . However, when these regions were part of a longer segment of viral RNA they induced much less RIG-I activation.",
